  "texts": [
    "One hypothesis arises from this observation-many of the potentially AI-influenced terms may have contributed to their overuse in ChatGPT, as these expressions gained popularity during the period of intensive LLM training.",
    "In other words, ChatGPT may have accelerated the inevitable temporal changes in writing in research.",
    "However, this hypothesis would be difficult to verify, since we cannot observe a parallel universe where ChatGPT does not exist.",
    "Interestingly, some of the common academic phrases used as controls also deviated in their proportion of use in 2024.",
    "The four phrases 'occurrence of', 'these findings', 'have shown', and 'interaction between' significantly increased in frequency of use in 2024, but since they are all very commonly used expressions in academic writing, it would be difficult for us humans to recognize that their frequency has increased."
